        <p>
          Baking is one of my quiet joys — a creative process rooted in comfort, memory, and a deep love for food that warms the heart. It’s also something I never thought I’d get into. In fact, I still struggle with calling myself a baker.
        </p>
        <p>
          What used to put me off — the chemistry, the precision, the patience — are the very reasons I now indulge in it. I’ve even started venturing into bread making, particularly sourdough, for the challenge and the unmatched smell of fresh loaves filling the house.
        </p>
        <p>
          My biggest pull to bake is the opportunity to share it. As someone without much of a sweet tooth, I find joy in making treats for others — it’s the sharing that gives me permission to keep baking. My personal favorite? A classic New York cheesecake. But I also love the adventure of trying to master things like macarons, even if they drive me slightly mad.
        </p>
